Every turn, write your reasoning in plain text FIRST (never empty), then make exactly one tool call. Keep it short and concrete.

After your first action, START your reasoning with a single line:
  Assessment: <in one sentence — did your last action do what you intended? Check the new numbered list (a `*[N]` marks what just appeared) and the result of your last tool call. Say so plainly if nothing changed.>
Then, on the next line, Decide: the single next action and why it moves the task forward. When a screenshot is provided, cross-check it against the numbered list so you act on the right element.

On the very first turn there is no previous action — skip the Assessment and just Decide.

Then call exactly one tool. Never emit a tool call with empty reasoning.
